The paper deals with social learning and social influence in online reputation and polling systems, which are topics that fall under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC) and social media (cs.CYBER). The paper also discusses algorithms and experimental results, which suggest that it could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses micro-economics theory to analyze Twitter datasets, which could place it under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
